• Method can return a value by using a return statement
• Return type of the method can not be void, need to be a data type

return method: return type is not void. we can use it for returning a value from return methods. MUST return a value.
used for exiting the method.
return anyData;

branching statements:
	continue; skiping the current iteration
	break; exits the loop or switch
	return anyData; exiting the method (one method, current method)
	System.exit(0); exits the system (EVERY THING WILL BE TERMINATED)
